event.title: November 4, 2008, the village of Rochester voted

data.event: On November 4, 2008, the village of Rochester voted to consolidate with the town of Rochester.
When they arrived in what is now Rochester there was nothing but dense virgin forest and wild prairie.

event.title: constructed farms and government buildings all within the first few months

data.event: They laid out post routes, built roads, constructed farms and government buildings all within the first few months of settling in what is now Rochester.
